Package: timeloops
Title: Self-Reporting Loops with Progress, Timing and Parallelism
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Giovanni", "Tinervia", , "giovannitinervia9@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Loops for 'for', 'while', and 'repeat' that report their own
    progress while they run, printing the iteration count, elapsed time, and an
    estimated time to completion (for 'for' loops). Run sequentially they are
    drop-in replacements that leave loop behaviour unchanged, including 'next'
    and 'break' statements. The 'for' loop can also be run in parallel across
    several cores, on all platforms and without manual cluster setup, showing a
    live progress bar whose appearance can be customised through the 'progressr'
    package.
